MESSAGE.value: Fixed a bug in the deserialization of write headers

Now send messages in such a way that multiple messages can be sent in rapid succession without waiting for an ACK / response of the corresponding write header. Also added an additional mechanism to make sure write headers with the same contents from the same user can be distinguished from one another
Fixed a bug that where the writeRecvQueue wasn't actually being written to or read from.
Fixed a bug that where the writeRecvQueue wasn't actually being written to.
Fixed a bug caused by the channels map in Client not being populated.
